          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 5 feet, *Reach (Long):* 5 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 160,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "20f6f5f93a453f3006eb194c6d712042",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Undead",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Once living, these creatures were infused after death with void energy and soul-corrupting unholy magic. When reduced to 0 Hit Points, an undead creature is destroyed. Undead creatures are damaged by vitality energy and are healed by void energy, and don\u2019t benefit from healing vitality effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "defense": {
      "ac": {
        "subtype": "armor_class",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "value": 21
      },
      "automatic_abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "stupefied 1",
              "aonid": 94,
              "game-obj": "Conditions",
              "name": "stupefied 1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "concentrate",
              "aonid": 561,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "concentrate",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Aura of Sobs",
          "range": {
            "range": 10,
            "subtype": "range",
            "text": "10 feet",
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "unit": "feet"
          },
          "saving_throw": [
            {
              "dc": 19,
              "save_type": "Will",
              "subtype": "save_dc",
              "text": "DC 19 Will save",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "An attic whisperer enshrouds itself in a tapestry of stolen voices. Each living creature that enters or starts their turn in the aura must succeed at a DC 19 Will save or the unnerving, bitter sobs render them distraught and they become stupefied 1 for as long as they remain within the aura. A creature that succeeds is temporarily immune for 1 hour. The attic whisperer can activate or deactivate the aura with a single action, which has the concentrate trait.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 16,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Auditory",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 206,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "5315505cfd3f3ba2685e9747898193b2",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Aura",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An aura is an emanation that continually ebbs out from you, affecting creatures within a certain radius. Aura can also refer to the magical signature of an item.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 60,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "fb5f8b3d849b073e1514a6a025810470",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Emotion",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 455,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This effect alters a creature\u2019s emotions. Effects with this trait always have the mental trait as well. Creatures with special training or that have mechanical or artificial intelligence are immune to emotion effects.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 106,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6a1f80610baa3617c1597f49c6406313",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Mental",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "A mental effect can alter the target\u2019s mind. It has no effect on an object or a mindless creature.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 120,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "a9126c150baeaac5ec247ce82c9b8ce2",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Occult",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 459,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the occult tradition, calling upon bizarre and ephemeral mysteries. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to occult magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "action_type": {
            "name": "Reaction",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
